title: Tomorrowland 2025 - Tiesto, Avicii, Martin Garrix, Meduza, David Guetta, Gigi D'Agostino, Axwell
description: Get ready to relive the magic or prepare for an unforgettable journey to Tomorrowland 2025! This epic video brings together an unparalleled lineup of electronic music legends and global superstars. Experience the electrifying beats of Tiesto, the timeless melodies of Avicii, the undeniable energy of Martin Garrix, the captivating sounds of Meduza, the mainstage mastery of David Guetta, the iconic anthems of Gigi D'Agostino, and the progressive power of Axwell. Prepare for a musical odyssey that transcends genres and generations, showcasing why Tomorrowland is the world's premier electronic music festival. From euphoric drops to mind-blowing visuals, this is your ultimate pre-game or post-festival fix. Don't miss out on the ultimate dance music experience! Witness history as Bury Your Dead, Massachusetts‚Äô own hardcore bruisers, deliver their final performance ever at the New England Metal & Hardcore Fest 2025. Known for their ferocious blend of hardcore, metalcore, and beatdown heaviness, Bury Your Dead rose to prominence in the early 2000s as one of New England‚Äôs most punishing exports.

Formed in Worcester, Massachusetts in 2001, the band quickly carved out a reputation with their relentless live shows and devastatingly heavy breakdowns. Their early releases like You Had Me at Hello (2003) and Cover Your Tracks (2004) set the tone, while Beauty and the Breakdown (2006) and Bury Your Dead (2008) cemented their place as a leading force in the metalcore/hardcore scene. Known for their innovative use of concept albums ‚Äî including tracks named after Tom Cruise movies and fairy tales ‚Äî Bury Your Dead balanced brutality with creativity, making them stand out in a crowded scene.

Despite lineup changes and years of relentless touring, the band remained an undeniable live powerhouse. With Mat Bruso‚Äôs signature growls, Eric Ellis‚Äô crushing riffs, and their no-nonsense stage presence, they became staples at major festivals and hardcore tours worldwide.

This headlining farewell show marks the end of an era for New England hardcore. Captured live at the New England Metal & Hardcore Fest, it‚Äôs a raw, emotional, and unforgettable final chapter from a band that inspired a generation of heavy music fans.

Stay connected with the legacy of Bury Your Dead and explore their catalog across streaming platforms ‚Äî the music lives on even after the final note fades.

title: The PEOPLE HAVE SPOKEN...This Show is Being RETIRED...Enjoy the Final Episode! | Professor of Rock
description:
Go to https://buyraycon.com/PROFESSOROFROCKOPEN to get 20% off sitewide. Thanks to Raycon for sponsoring!

Coming up, it's our final edition of Test of Time. Where go back to a golden year in rock and look at the entire top 40 and tell you what the real top songs are decades later. We have some of the biggest rock bands ever here to help us count these down, including legendary Foreigner frontman Lou Gramm, who was struggling to get his vocals recorded at his session until the most beautiful woman he‚Äôd ever seen walked into the studio and sat down to watch him. It inspired a vocal that became one of the greatest ever put down then rushed out of the booth to track the girl down and he NEVER saw her again! Who was the mystery woman? We also have Don't Stop Believin', a song that Neal Schon played a solo on in the first 40 seconds of, and the label bosses said no way!  They tried to erase it, but the guitarist said tough crap, he fought ‚Äòem, and it stayed in‚Ä¶ the song didn‚Äôt do a well as the band thought it would but 40 plus years later it became the biggest song of all time. Then there‚Äôs Working for the Weekend, where Mike Reno accidentally sang the wrong lyrics when he was recording it‚Ä¶the mistake made the song one of the biggest of the 80s. Plus, the Badass opening baseline from Under Pressure that defined the 80s when everyone and their dog ripped it off‚Ä¶ It‚Äôs all next on for.

#classicrock  #80smusic  #vinylstory #onehitwonder 

Okay so for this episode of Test of Time, let‚Äôs see if you can guess what year I‚Äôm covering. In movie theaters Rocky Balboa was chasing that Eye of the Tiger and taking on Clubber Lang for the third installment of the Rocky series. ET the Extra-Terrestrial was ready to phone home and you could catch Harrison Ford starring in the Ridley Scott film Blade Runner.nOn television you could watch the debuts of Late Night with David Letterman, Knight Rider, and Cheers. Time Magazine named the Personal Computer the ‚ÄúMachine of the Year‚Äù instead of ‚ÄúMan of the Year,‚Äù and the first commercial CDs and CD Players were released in Japan. Do you know the year? ‚Ä¶It was 1982.

For the show we're revisiting this very same week from 1982 to find out which Top 40 hits from the Billboard Hot 100 have truly stood the test of time and become the biggest songs from that era. And we‚Äôre going to count ‚Äòem down in honor of my hero Casey Kasem.  Ok we‚Äôre gonna play a game‚Ä¶I‚Äôm going to play you 3 seconds of the big songs on our countdown and then you try to guess what the top songs are decades later‚Ä¶. To figure which song is the Test of Time winner, I‚Äôve totaled up the streaming numbers from the platforms like Spotify and YouTube. And along the way I‚Äôll tell you where each song ranked back in 1982.

First on the countdown, in at #10 with a 180 million streams, it‚Äôs Physical by Olivia Newton John. So this week in 1982, Olivia was rocking it at #1, part of her 10 consecutive week run at the top of the Billboard Hot 100, and of course the American Top 40. Physical was like an unstoppable freight train barreling down the tracks. Everyone else just had to get out of the way. Olivia was of course no stranger to chart success. She had a killer run through the 70s, which included #1 hits like "I Honestly Love You" and starring opposite John Travolta in Grease. By the way, the soundtrack for Grease gave her three Top 5 hits, including the #1 hit You‚Äôre the One That I Want, ONJ was on a tear and quickly becoming a global superstar. And now it was time to take on the 80s‚Ä¶

 According to Kipner, the idea was to write a song about the physical side of love, and bypass the emotional side of things. The stories of Under Pressure by Queen and David Bowie including Freddie Mercury, Don't Stop Believin' by Journey, Waiting for a Girl Like You Foreigner, Turn it On Again by Genesis and Phil Collins,  Working for the Weekend by Loverboy, Centerfold by J Geils Band,  Let's Groove by Earth Wind and Fire,  I Can't Go for that By Daryl Hall and John Oates,  and Leather and Lace By Stevie Nicks and Don Henley.

title: Bury Your Dead Final Show Ever |  Hardcore Legends at New England Metal & Hardcore Fest 2025 Part 1
description:
Part 2: https://youtu.be/XJ4sVENrQ40?si=NPYw1hMQouhVVRM7

Witness history as Bury Your Dead, Massachusetts‚Äô own hardcore bruisers, deliver their final performance ever at the New England Metal & Hardcore Fest 2025. Known for their ferocious blend of hardcore, metalcore, and beatdown heaviness, Bury Your Dead rose to prominence in the early 2000s as one of New England‚Äôs most punishing exports.

Formed in Worcester, Massachusetts in 2001, the band quickly carved out a reputation with their relentless live shows and devastatingly heavy breakdowns. Their early releases like You Had Me at Hello (2003) and Cover Your Tracks (2004) set the tone, while Beauty and the Breakdown (2006) and Bury Your Dead (2008) cemented their place as a leading force in the metalcore/hardcore scene. Known for their innovative use of concept albums ‚Äî including tracks named after Tom Cruise movies and fairy tales ‚Äî Bury Your Dead balanced brutality with creativity, making them stand out in a crowded scene.

Despite lineup changes and years of relentless touring, the band remained an undeniable live powerhouse. With Mat Bruso‚Äôs signature growls, Eric Ellis‚Äô crushing riffs, and their no-nonsense stage presence, they became staples at major festivals and hardcore tours worldwide.

This headlining farewell show marks the end of an era for New England hardcore. Captured live at the New England Metal & Hardcore Fest, it‚Äôs a raw, emotional, and unforgettable final chapter from a band that inspired a generation of heavy music fans.

Stay connected with the legacy of Bury Your Dead and explore their catalog across streaming platforms ‚Äî the music lives on even after the final note fades.

Comment below with your favorite Bury Your Dead album, song, or memory, and share what this band has meant to you. Let‚Äôs send them off with the respect and energy they‚Äôve given us for over two decades.

title: Rose Breaks the Axe to Save Jack üî®üö¢‚ù§Ô∏è | Titanic BTS Behind the Rescue
description:
Rose Breaks the Axe to Save Jack üî®üö¢‚ù§Ô∏è | Titanic BTS Behind the Rescue

This behind-the-scenes footage reveals how filmmakers created the intense handcuffs rescue moment where Rose uses an axe to free Jack during the Titanic flooding sequence. Instead of a single clean strike like in the movie, the BTS shows Kate Winslet rehearsing the swing dozens of times while Leonardo DiCaprio stayed strapped to a stunt handcuff rig.
Special effects teams built multiple ‚Äúbreakaway‚Äù axes with softened metal, allowing the blade to bend safely on impact while still looking real on camera. The rising water level came from high-pressure pumps flooding the set every few minutes, forcing the actors to work in freezing water while stunt divers and safety crews stayed just below the surface.
James Cameron coordinated every beat, from the water surge to Rose‚Äôs swing timing to Jack‚Äôs reactions. Seeing the actors reset, laugh, and brace for another cold take gives fans a brand-new appreciation for this unforgettable rescue scene.

Red Dead Redemption 2 is a 2018 action-adventure game developed and published by Rockstar Games. The game is the third entry in the Red Dead series and a prequel to the 2010 game Red Dead Redemption. The story is set in a fictionalized representation of the United States in 1899 and follows the exploits of Arthur Morgan, an outlaw and member of the Van der Linde gang, who must deal with the decline of the Wild West while attempting to survive against government forces, rival gangs, and other adversaries. The game is presented through first- and third-person perspectives, and the player may freely roam in its interactive open world. Gameplay elements include shootouts, robberies, hunting, horseback riding, interacting with non-player characters, and maintaining the character's honor rating through moral choices and deeds. A bounty system governs the response of law enforcement and bounty hunters to crimes committed by the player.

The game's development lasted over eight years, beginning soon after Red Dead Redemption's release, and it became one of the most expensive video games ever made. Rockstar co-opted all of its studios into one large team to facilitate development. They drew influence from real locations as opposed to film or art, focused on creating an accurate reflection of the time with the game's characters and world. The game was Rockstar's first built specifically for eighth-generation consoles, having tested their technical capabilities while porting Grand Theft Auto V. The game's soundtrack features an original score composed by Woody Jackson and several vocal tracks produced by Daniel Lanois. Development included a crunch schedule of 100-hour weeks, leading to reports of mandatory and unpaid overtime. Red Dead Online, the game's online multiplayer mode, lets up to 32 players engage in a variety of cooperative and competitive game modes.

Red Dead Redemption 2 was released for the PlayStation 4 and Xbox One in October 2018, and for Windows and Stadia in November 2019. It broke several records and had the second-biggest launch in the history of entertainment, generating US$725 million in sales from its opening weekend and exceeding the lifetime sales of Red Dead Redemption in two weeks. The game received critical acclaim, with praise directed at its story, characters, open world, graphics, music, and level of detail, but some criticism at its control scheme and emphasis on realism over player freedom. It won more than 175 Game of the Year awards and received multiple other accolades from awards shows and gaming publications. It is considered one of eighth-generation console gaming's most significant titles and among the greatest video games ever made. It is among the best-selling video games with over 65 million copies shipped. #cowboys #crowdcontrol

title: Watch Ozzy Osbourne on stage for poignant final show with Black Sabbath weeks before death aged 76
description:
OZZY Osbourne joined Black Sabbath on stage for a poignant final show just weeks before his death aged 76.

The rock legend arrived on stage at Villa Park in Birmingham, dressed in his trademark black, in what was his last ever performance earlier this month.

The crowd were heard roaring with excitement as the rock legend entered while sat for the historic gig on July 5.

Ozzy sang with his fellow founding fathers of heavy metal while seated on a black bat throne.

His performance at the show, Called Back To The Beginning, was sadly the rock veteran's last time performing on stage.

title: The Story of Ozzy Osbourne‚Äôs Final Show
description:
I was in Birmingham for Ozzy Osbourne‚Äôs final concert, and this video is my story of what it was like to witness the end of an era. From the streets of Birmingham ‚Äî the birthplace of Black Sabbath ‚Äî to the arena where the Prince of Darkness gave his last performance, this is part documentary, part tribute, and part fan experience. Was Ozzy crazy or a genius all along? This final show might just give us the answer.

00:00 - Intro
00:51 - Chapter I - Ozzy Zig Needs Gig
03:34 - Chapter II - Satanist or Opportunist? 
06:22 - Chapter III - Bat... Man?
07:29 - Chapter IV - The Original Kardashian?
10:24 - Chapter V - The Final Show
11:43 - Chapter VI - Iron Man

Ozzy Osbourne has defined heavy metal for over 50 years. From his days with Black Sabbath to a solo career filled with legendary tracks like Crazy Train, Mr. Crowley, and No More Tears, Ozzy became more than a frontman ‚Äî he became an icon. This video captures not just the final concert, but the legacy of Ozzy Osbourne, the atmosphere in Birmingham, and what it means to say goodbye to the man who changed rock history.

If you‚Äôre a fan of Ozzy Osbourne, Black Sabbath, Tony Iommi, Geezer Butler, Bill Ward, heavy metal history, final concerts, Birmingham music, or rock documentaries, this video is for you.

I went to Villa Park in Aston, Birmingham, in the United Kingdom, to see Ozzy's hometown and his final show -- Back To The Beginning. 

A bit of a departure from our usual movie/TV-centric content, sure, but since Ozzy's MTV show The Osbournes was a big part of his career, I think it fits.

‚ö° Witness Sum 41 perform the title track ‚ÄúUnderclass Hero‚Äù from their 2007 album Underclass Hero, live at their final Toronto show on Jan. 30, 2025! Formed in 1996 in Ajax, Ontario, Sum 41 is a Canadian rock band known for their infectious blend of punk and alternative rock. Formed in 2008, the group consists of Œ£KIYM (violin), mitchel (VJ/video), KazPhantasmo_V (bass), and Gan (guitar, tabla). In live performances, they are supported by drums, percussion, and didgeridoo, creating a hybrid club sound that fuses live instrumentation, electronic audio, and visual production, centered around "human-powered techno" and "human-powered trance." The VJ's visual effects synchronize with the music to craft an immersive live space that captivates all five senses. The group has also released numerous tracks featuring vocals.

In addition to performing at major domestic festivals, the group has expanded internationally, including a tour in Taiwan in 2019, and has remained consistently active since its formation. They have received high praise at events such as DJ BAKU‚Äôs KAIKOO MUSIC FESTIVAL.

In 2024, they released their 4th album, Yoru Nomad. In March 2025, they followed up with a 12-inch vinyl edition titled Yoru Nomad ‚Äì Gold Vinyl. Yoru Nomad explores themes such as ‚Äúcommuning with the night through oscillating repetition,‚Äù ‚Äúregeneration and resonance,‚Äù and ‚Äúreconstructing Detroit techno grooves from dismantled Hindu music.‚Äù It portrays a journey through time and space‚Äînight as a crossroads between people and sound‚Äîexpressing contrasts of darkness and light, life and rebirth, and the inner and outer journeys of the ‚Äúnomad.‚Äù

In December 2025, they released a collaborative single titled Keizoku to Hanpuku (‚ÄúContinuity and Repetition‚Äù) with the band Akarakime (Akarakime Rareta Koibitotachi e). Continuously seeking new modes of expression, they continue to evolve uniquely within the live music scene both in Japan and abroad.

title: Live: An immersive view of Nanxun ancient town as a pearl of Jiangnan
description:
Nanxun ancient town, a historic core of Huzhou in Zhejiang province, is celebrated for its premium silk and a heritage that seamlessly blends commerce, scholarship and cultural confluence. With a history spanning nearly 800 years, this water town is woven with canals, arched bridges and architecture that fuses the gentle elegance of Jiangnan with diverse decorative influences. Preserved traditional crafts further highlight its distinctive charm.
As Zhejiang prepares to host a sub-venue for the 2026 Spring Festival Gala, Nanxun stands out as a luminous symbol of Jiangnan's timeless cultural allure and its spirit of cultural integration. #SpringFestival2026

description:
This video walks through the steps to fix a mandolin pickup jack that has become loose or completely dislodged.  It walks through the process of removing the strings, fishing the jack back through the cut out, how to set the distance for inside nut, guiding it back into place, and setting up the floating bridge back to the correct location.  

The same steps could be used to replace a mandolin pickup with a new one.

Giorgio Armani's emotional final fashion show before death
description:
Giorgio Armani's emotional final fashion show before death

#breakingnews #giorgioarmani #rip #entertainment 

In his final public appearance, Giorgio Armani closed his Armani Prive couture show in January. It was the last time the legendary fashion designer, who died at the age of 91, would farewell the catwalk.

‚ÄúWith infinite sorrow, the Armani Group announces the passing of its creator, founder, and tireless driving force: Giorgio Armani,‚Äù his fashion house, Armani, said in a statement.

He passed away peacefully at home surrounded by his family.

Well-wishers will be able to pay their respects at a funeral chamber across the weekend in Milan, while a private funeral will be held for him at an unspecified date.

The pioneering designer had built his mammoth fashion empire over 50 years and was the creative director, CEO and sole shareholder of the iconic brand until his death. The self-confessed workaholic had once remarked that his ‚Äúgreatest weakness‚Äù was that he was ‚Äúin control of everything‚Äù, and had confessed his biggest regret in life was ‚Äúspending too many hours working and not enough with friends and family‚Äù.

Armani‚Äôs passing came just weeks ahead of a planned 50th anniversary celebration which was scheduled to happen during Milan Fashion Week.

‚ÄòToday, with deep emotion, we feel the void left by the one who founded and nurtured this family with vision, passion, and dedication,‚Äù a spokesman said.

The designer had dressed celebrities including Cate Blanchett, Nicole Kidman and Lady Gaga for many red carpet events across his lengthy career, and was a regular fixture in Hollywood circles.

Born in 1934 in Piacenza, Italy, Armani initially pursued a career in medicine before enrolling in the army in his early twenties. His first stint in fashion was as a window dresser at the Milan department store La Rinascente in 1957.

In the 1960s, Armani designed menswear for Nino Cerruti and also freelanced for a number of other fashion houses before launching his own namesake brand in 1975 with both menswear and womenswear collections.

From there, Armani began to rapidly diversify his company, launching Giorgio Armani swimwear, underwear and accessories lines before introducing fragrances, Armani Jeans and Emporio Armani in the early 1980s. Around the same time, he began creating clothing for the big screen, famously designing the costumes for 1980s ‚ÄúAmerican Gigolo,‚Äù among many other films.

He also set up shop on Rodeo Drive in Beverly Hills, hiring LA-based reporter Wanda McDaniel to handle VIP outreach. In 1978, Diane Keaton accepted her Best Actress Oscar for Annie Hall in an oversized beige Armani blazer her character might‚Äôve loved, and became the first Hollywood star to wear the brand on the red carpet.

title: Ryan Reynolds Crashes Hugh Jackman's Final Show at Radio City Music Hall - "Fly Me to the Moon"
description:
A "Deadpool & Wolverine" reunion happened live on stage at Radio City Music Hall during the final show of Hugh Jackman Live: From New York with Love, the Australian performer's NYC residency. As the show approached its final set of songs, Hugh Jackman spotted a misplaced face in his orchestra, Ryan Reynolds, who joked about paying off one of the horn players to teach him to play. Hugh asks Ryan to prove it, and he pretends to play "My Funny Valentine" before Jackman continues with the show, diving into "Fly Me to the Moon." After the song, as Jackman began his moment of gratitude to his band, he again called out his Marvel co-star.

HEATHROW AIRPORT LIVE

From Heathrow‚Äôs perimeter to airports around the world, Big Jet TV has built a reputation as the No1 destination for live aviation coverage on YouTube and is the UK‚Äôs leading aviation live streaming channel, bringing the thrill of real-time aircraft action to viewers worldwide. 

Founded in 2016 by aviation enthusiast Jerry Dyer, the channel has transformed how people experience aviation from the ground with high-energy commentary, professional filming, and immersive live broadcasts.

At the heart of Big Jet TV‚Äôs coverage is London Heathrow Airport (LHR), the UK‚Äôs busiest aviation hub. From carefully chosen vantage points around the runways‚Äîincluding perimeter roads and exclusive spots‚Äîviewers enjoy close-up coverage of airport movements, takeoffs and dramatic approaches. One of its most iconic setups is our Ford Transit van fitted with a custom filming platform, enabling Jerry to move quickly depending on operations. 

The channel became a global sensation during Storm Eunice in 2022, when millions tuned in to watch pilots battle hurricane-force crosswinds at Heathrow. The viral broadcast cemented Big Jet TV as the premier destination for live aviation streaming, attracting both aviation enthusiasts and mainstream audiences.

Beyond Heathrow, the channel also streams from UK military bases showcasing fighter jets and military operations. Internationally, Big Jet TV provides coverage from airports across Europe, the United States, Japan and Australia. broadening its reach to a truly global community.

We operate a hybrid model: free livestreams twice a week from Heathrow, plus optional memberships offering exclusive overseas shows, access to chat, and behind-the-scenes extras. 

More than just plane spotting: the channel delivers an immersive aviation experience, combining the adrenaline of real-time aircraft movements with Jerry‚Äôs humorous and knowledgeable commentary. Big Jet TV offers unmatched excitement for aviation fans.

Titles/descriptions alone do NOT make a live go viral, especially for a small channel. Zero views last time doesn‚Äôt mean you did something wrong.

Why you got 0 views (very common, not your fault)

description:
#SamuraiJack #JackTheSamurai #Aku #GenndyTartakovsky #PhilLaMarr #MakoIwamatsu #GregBaldwin #TimeTravel #AnimatedSeries #CartoonNetwork #AdultSwim #ActionAdventure #MartialArts #EpicQuest #SamuraiVsAku #JackVsAku #FuturisticWorld #AncientWarrior #SciFiFantasy #JapaneseSamurai #AnimatedAction #EmmyAwardWinning #MinimalistArtStyle #EpicSoundtrack #LegendarySamurai #FifthSeason #Season5 #DarkAnimation #HeroicJourney #SwordOfJack #TalkingDogs #TheScotsman #Ashi #DaughtersOfAku #RobotAssassins #ShapeShiftingMasterOfDarkness #FlashbackScenes #StylizedCombat #AnimatedViolence #DeepPhilosophy #RevengeAndRedemption #LostInTime #FinalBattle #AnimatedMasterpiece #CultClassic #SamuraiJackReboot #EmotionalStorytelling #VoiceActingLegend #RetroAnimation #JackReturns
Samurai Jack is an American animated action-adventure television series created by Genndy Tartakovsky. Originally airing on Cartoon Network from 2001 to 2004, and later concluding with a final season on Adult Swim in 2017, the show is widely regarded as a masterpiece of animation, storytelling, and visual style.
The series follows Jack, a noble samurai prince from feudal Japan who wields a magical sword capable of defeating evil. Just as he is about to vanquish Aku‚Äîa shape-shifting demon and master of darkness‚ÄîJack is flung into a dystopian future ruled by Aku himself. Trapped in this nightmarish world, Jack journeys across time, battling countless enemies and helping those oppressed by Aku‚Äôs reign, all while searching for a way back to the past to undo the future that is Aku.
What sets Samurai Jack apart is its minimalist storytelling, striking visuals, stylized combat sequences, and emotional depth. It blends elements of science fiction, fantasy, martial arts, and mythology, often using silence, atmosphere, and music to convey powerful moments instead of dialogue.
The show stars Phil LaMarr as the voice of Jack and originally featured Mako Iwamatsu (later Greg Baldwin) as the voice of Aku. Its fifth and final season took on a darker, more mature tone, giving closure to Jack‚Äôs long journey in a powerful and emotional finale.
Samurai Jack is a unique blend of action and artistry‚Äîa cult classic that continues to influence animation and storytelling around the world.
